{"questionId":"9067835","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The following shows some compounds which can be made from ethene, C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">ethene (C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>) → C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>5</sub>Cl → C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>6</sub>O → C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>O</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State the type of reaction which converts ethene into C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>5</sub>Cl.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«electrophilic» addition ✔ </span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"> NOTE: Do <strong>not</strong> accept “nucleophilic addition” or “free radical addition”.<br>Do <strong>not</strong> accept “halogenation”.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067835","referenceCode":"19N.2.sl.TZ0.3a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the type of reaction which converts ethene into C2H5Cl.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}